<h3>Research &gt; Online Resources  &gt; Colleges &amp; Financial Aid</h3>


<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>In addition to these  websites, a search for the subject <strong>&ldquo;college&rdquo;</strong> in the Library&rsquo;s online catalog will result in listings that include <strong>eBooks</strong> that may be downloaded to your  computer or mobile device. The <em>eMedia  Library</em> may also be searched with the keyword &ldquo;<strong>college</strong>.&quot;</p>
<p><br>
  Other useful words for  searching the Library catalog are &ldquo;<strong>college  choice</strong>&rdquo;, and &ldquo;<strong>universities</strong>&rdquo;.  Many books on college choice, applications, testing, costs; and assistance with  the GED, are shelved with call numbers starting with <strong>378</strong>.<strong> </strong></p>
<h4>College Choice &amp;  Financial Aid</h4>
<ul class="resource_list">
<li>  <a href="https://nces.ed.gov/surveys/ctes/tables/index.asp?LEVEL=COLLEGE"><strong>Career/Technical  Education Statistics</strong></a> &ndash; National Center for Education Statistics data relating to  enrollment at various postsecondary facilities; how much it costs, how they are  funding their education, demographics, programs of study.</li>

<li><a href="https://nces.ed.gov/collegenavigator/"><strong>College  Navigator</strong></a> &ndash; The National Center for Education Statistics collects data  on all topics relating to education in the United States as well as   worldwide. The site is designed to help students choose a college.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.collegesource.org"><strong>College  Source Online</strong></a> &ndash; Over 35,000 complete  college catalogs and home pages, plus a school match feature.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.collegetoolkit.com/"><strong>College  Toolkit</strong></a> &ndash; Allows students to find  and apply for scholarships, search through a database of more than 4,000  colleges, and explore 900 careers all in one location. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.collegezone.com"><strong>College Zone</strong></a> &ndash; Powered by the  Illinois Student Assistance Commission (ISAC), College Zone is the trusted  source of college planning information for Illinois colleges and universities.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.collegenet.com"><strong>CollegeNet</strong></a> &ndash; Guide to colleges,  universities, graduate programs, and financial aid.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.fastweb.com/"><strong>FastWeb (Financial Aid Search  Through the Web)</strong></a> &ndash; This  is a searchable database of over 180,000 scholarships,  grants, loans and fellowships. You can set up a personal profile to search  against, and fastWEB will notify you of new sources that match your profile when  they are added to the database.</li>

<li><a href="https://studentaid.ed.gov/"><strong>Federal  Student Aid</strong></a> &ndash; The U.S. Department of  Education's student aid website, a &quot;one-stop shop&quot; for up-to-date and  accurate data on federal aid available to help you pay for college.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.fafsa.ed.gov"><strong>Financial Aid for Students (FAFSA)</strong></a> &ndash; The Free Application  for Federal Student Aid (known as FAFSA), is a form that must be filled out  annually by university students (both undergraduate and graduate) and sometimes  their parents in the United States to determine their eligibility for federal  financial aid (including grants, loans, and work-study programs).</li>

<li><a href="https://studentaid.ed.gov/students/publications/student_guide/index.html"><strong>Funding  Your Education</strong></a> &ndash; This guide to federal student aid provides  a description of federal student aid programs from the U.S. Department of  Education, including grants, loans, and work-study. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.gocollege.com"><strong>Go College</strong></a> &ndash; Find a college search, scholarship search and SAT/ACT practice tests,  plus links to college life sites.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.isac.org/students/"><strong>Illinois  Student Assistance Commission</strong></a>&nbsp; -This site has financial  aid information provided by a group whose goal it is to make college accessible  and affordable for Illinois students.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.bls.gov/ooh/"><strong>Occupational Outlook Handbook</strong></a> &ndash; A classic reference  about occupations from A to Z. Compiled by the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.petersons.com"><strong>Peterson's Education Resource</strong></a> &ndash; Information about  colleges and universities, career schools, graduate programs, distance learning,  executive training, private secondary schools, summer opportunities, study  abroad, financial aid, test preparation, and career exploration.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.princetonreview.com"><strong>Princeton Review</strong></a> &ndash; Explore schools and  careers, prepare for standardized tests and entrance exams, research  scholarships and financial aid options.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.princetonreview.com/schoolsearch.aspx?sch=College"><strong>Princeton Review School Finder</strong></a> &ndash; Search for  information on a specific college.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.finaid.org"><strong>Smart  Student Guide to Financial Aid</strong></a> &ndash; This award-winning site has grown into the most comprehensive  annotated collection of information about student financial aid on the web.</li>

<li><a href="https://colleges.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-colleges"><strong>U.S. News College Rankings</strong></a> &ndash; Rankings of colleges  and universities from U.S. News and World Report.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Test Preparation</h4>
<ul class="resource_list">
<li>  <a href="https://www.collegeboard.org"><strong>College Board</strong></a> &ndash; Collegeboard.com  offers online SAT registration and SAT score sending, and SAT test preparation  with  SAT questions. Learn about classes you may be eligible to test out  of and still receive college credit.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.gocollege.com"><strong>Go College</strong></a> &ndash; Find a college search, scholarship search and SAT/ACT practice tests,  plus links to college life sites.</li>

<li><a href="https://rpa.warrenville.com/rpa/default/webauth.htm?rs=LExpress" target="_blank"><strong>LearningExpress</strong></a> &ndash; Interactive tutorials  and practice tests to help users prepare for high-stakes tests such as the GED,  GRE, ACT, and SAT. The platform can help prepare for a wide range of  career-oriented licensing and certification exams in health care, education,  civil service, and homeland security.&nbsp;<strong>This  database is available  remotely with your Warrenville Library card number and 4 digit PIN. </strong></li>

<li><a href="https://www.princetonreview.com"><strong>Princeton Review</strong></a> &ndash; Explore schools and  careers, prepare for standardized tests and entrance exams, research  scholarships and financial aid options.</li>


<li><a href="https://rpa.warrenville.com/rpa/default/webauth.htm?rs=tut"><strong>Tutor.com</strong></a> &ndash; Tutor.com is a free, on-demand online tutoring service that connects students in Kindergarten - 12th grade and  introductory college students to expert tutors in math, science, social studies  and English via the Internet. The Adult Learner section supports those earning  their GED, seeking grammar help with their resume and more. Live Homework Help  is available every day from 10 a.m. to midnight.&nbsp; Spanish-speaking tutors are  available in math, science, social studies and adult learning every day from10 a.m. to midnight.<strong> This  database is available  remotely with your Warrenville Library card number and 4 digit PIN. </strong></li>
</ul>

